## How to Login to PTF host 

From your host (where Docker runs):

docker exec -it ptf\_vms6-1 bash

You will get a shell inside the PTF container (usually as root).
No SSH or password is needed when using docker exec.

If you prefer SSH (only if the PTF image has SSH enabled):

ssh root\@10.250.0.102

Note:

*   Password is "root"
*   Often no password is required if key-based authentication is used

