## Hosting an HTTP Server on the PTF

Step 1: Enter the PTF container

docker exec -it ptf\_vms6-1 bash

Step 2: Run a simple HTTP server (Python 3)

Serve the current directory on port 8000 (all interfaces):

python3 -m http.server 8000 --bind 0.0.0.0

Serve a specific directory:

cd /path/to/your/files
python3 -m http.server 8000 --bind 0.0.0.0

***

